# Operator populates this file after dropping bastion-theatre*.rpm into this
# directory. Format: `<sha256>  <filename>` — one pair per line, two-space
# separator (standard `sha256sum` output). Example:
#
#     7a3f...c12e  bastion-theatre-0.0.0-1.fc43.x86_64.rpm
#     e88b...9034  bastion-theatre-manager-0.0.0-1.fc43.x86_64.rpm
#
# `make VARIANT=bastion-edge repo` runs `sha256sum -c EXPECTED_SHA256` before
# `createrepo` and aborts on any mismatch. If this file is empty or blank
# (comments-only like this default), the Makefile emits a WARN and continues
# — the sha check is opt-in per the variant README's supply-chain section.
